    {
      "href": "/benaaa/list/liminal-spaces/",
      "user": "benaaa",
      "slug": "liminal-spaces",
      "title": "liminal spaces",
      "desc": "spaces and places that capture transition, threshold, the in between, the after of what has been and the before of what is yet to come. locations we’re not supposed to form any identity at. locations we're normally familiar with but there’s something off about them. is it the lack of present people? or did we just pick an unusual time to be there? and why does this weird, ambivalent feeling of comfort and discomfort come up?\n\nhave we been here before?\n\n.\n.\n.\n.\n\ntv shows:\n- severance (2022- )\n- silo (2023- )\n- the good place (2016-2020)\n- the man on the inside (2024- )\n- superstore (2015-2021)\n- 1899 (2022- )\n- stranger things (2016- )\n- homecoming (2018-2020)\n- the oa (2016-2019)",
      "owner": "List by bena 🌙 PATRON",
      "tags": []
    },
